---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy" description="The BES3 privacy notice.">
  <section class="page-hero shell">
    <div><p class="eyebrow">LEGAL</p><h1>Privacy, in plain language.</h1></div><p class="lede">
      This page must be updated before launch to match the actual analytics, hosting, newsletter and
      form providers used by BES3.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="section reading-width article-body">
    <h2>What the static site stores</h2><p>
      The initial static site should not require accounts and should collect only the data needed
      for an explicitly requested contact or newsletter subscription.
    </p>
    <h2>Analytics</h2><p>
      Use privacy-conscious, aggregated analytics. If a provider uses cookies or processes personal
      data, name it here before production launch and provide the required consent controls.
    </p>
    <h2>Commercial link events</h2><p>
      Outbound click measurement must not include names, email addresses or user identifiers. It
      should record only the article, placement and link category needed to understand editorial
      performance.
    </p>
    <h2>Contact</h2><p>
      Privacy questions can be sent to <a href="mailto:editorial@bes3.com">editorial@bes3.com</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
